Who watched the sacred lessons of her tongue

For fairer prise , than such accomplished love
Each solemn requiem offered to his shade
the gaudy scenes of pomp and power
the far-retired grove , Once the blessed mansion of her happy love
that memory oft would raise A solemn prospect of those blooming days Aurelius gave
One pledge of love her comfort
That full of heavenborn dignity informs The mortal breast which ardent virtue warms

the wall , And arched windows with their blazon bright Shed through the herald glow a solemn light : There clad in rough habiliments of war Full many a hero bore a glorious scar ; There in the civic fur the sons of peace , Whose counsels bade their country's tumults cease ; While by their side , gracing the ancient scene , Hung gentle ladies of most comely mien
